D Note that here we don't allow Flash to create sinks
D or for sinks to accrete. We will create "sinks" which
D will represent MS stars without accretion, but it still
D allows us to use all the bridging stuff I wrote for
D sink particles already. - JW

PPDEFINE AMUSE_STARS

REQUIRES Particles/ParticlesMapping/Quadratic
REQUIRES flashUtilities/sorting/quicksort

D Here's a variable that holds the amount of time
D passed since a star was formed in this cell.

VARIABLE LSFT  TYPE: GENERIC

D low_dens_thres  minimum density for gas to be removed 
D                 (Default 10^4 n_H / cc)
D high_dens_thres maximum density which triggers the 
D                 removal of gas (Default 10^6 n_H /cc)
D min_mass        minimum mass star which can be returned 
D                 from the IMF sampling routine in MSun 
D                 (Default 1.0 MSun)


PARAMETER low_dens_thres        REAL   1.66e-20
PARAMETER high_dens_thres       REAL   1.66e-18
PARAMETER min_mass              REAL   1.0

D gaussian_sigma The spread in the gaussian profile
D                we use to smooth the gas density taken from cells
D                around where the new star particle is made
D                (using the sink particle functions).

D sfe            Local star formation efficiency (usually around 20-30%,
D                see Krumholz, Dekel and McKee 2011)

PARAMETER gaussian_sigma        REAL   1.3367
PARAMETER sfe                   REAL   0.3
